Description: Sherd of East Greek pottery open vase, perhaps a larger bowl; inside glazed with added red band lined in white; exterior: part of four bands preserved; graffito on exterior.
Curator's comments: Marked '12-37' in pencil and 'list 37' on label. Nearly joins 1965,0930.722
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.779)
